<text id="WB_KL-86">
    <metadata>
        <title>"Indian Clothes"</title>
        <author>Julia <alph>Starritt</alph></author>
        <date>1957</date>
        <publication>William Bright, <em>The Karok Language</em> (1957), pp. 300-301, Text
            86</publication>
    </metadata>
    <data>
        <paragraph>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="Indian dress"><m id="506">arara</m><m id="7028">yáfus</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5560">táfirapu</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made with"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2336">kyâar</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>The Indian dress was made of buckskin.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="the dress"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="7028">yáfus</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w><m id="7097">yítha</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w gl="deer skin"><m id="5135">pufích</m><m id="4148">maan</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>The dress was just one deerskin.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6383">vaa</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w gl="they were wrapped up in"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3653"
                            >iyxôorariv</m><m id="168">ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And they were just wrapped in it.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="their apron"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4264">mukun</m><m id="5644"
                            >tántaav</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5560">táfirapu</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made with"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2336">kyâar</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And their apron was made of buckskin.</eng>
            </s>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="their good dress"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4264">mukun</m><m id="7028"
                            >yafusa</m><m id="7066">yêepsha</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="7000">yâamach</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2348">kyâah</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And their good dresses were made pretty.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="4978">píshiip</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4537">panyúrar</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was braided on"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="5764">taxapkóo</m><m id="168"
                            >hi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>First bear-lily leaves were braided on.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="1016">axyúus</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made with"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2336">kyâar</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">ti</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="7263">yuxtháran</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5308">sápruuk</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made with"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2336">kyâar</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>It was made with digger-pine nuts and abalone shell and it was made with
                    olivella shells.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="7263">yuxtháran</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6156">tûupichas</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was sliced"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="5652">tapakpák</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>The abalone shell was chopped up small.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="their dress"><m id="4264">mukun</m><m id="7028">yáfus</m></w>
                    <w gl="not long"><m id="5082">pu</m><m id="6397">vâarama</m><m id="5201"
                            >sa</m><m id="1371">hara</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Their dresses were not long.</eng>
            </s>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="their hat"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4264">mukun</m><m id="483"
                            >'ápxaan</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made with"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2336">kyâar</m><m id="168"
                            >ahi</m><m id="6035">ti</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5323">sárip</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5333">sárum</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Their hats were made with hazel twigs and pine-roots.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="they were decorated with"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="2311"
                            >ikxúrikara</m><m id="6035">ti</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4537">panyúrar</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="2013">ikritápkir</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6052">tíiptiip</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>They were decorated with bear-lily leaves and five-finger fern and chain
                    fern.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="the chain fern"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="6052">tíiptiip</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="78">aaxkúnish</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was made"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2348">kyâa</m><m id="168">hi</m><m
                            id="6035">tih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And the chain fern was made red.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="their hat"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4264">mukun</m><m id="483"
                            >'ápxaan</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w gl="it was woven"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="6545">vík</m><m id="168">ahi</m><m
                            id="6035">ti</m></w>
                    <w gl="the Jeffrey pine root"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="5333">sárum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4281">mûuk</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w gl="the beargrass"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="4537">panyúrar</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w gl="the five-finger fern"><m id="4407">p</m><m id="2013">eekritápkir</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w gl="the chain fern"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="6052">tíiptiip</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And their hats were woven with the pine-roots and the bear-lily leaves and the
                    five-finger fern and the chain fern.</eng>
            </s>
        </paragraph>
    </data>
